Here's a comprehensive summary of the search results related to **Storybook 10, Angular, `setCompodocJson`, `@storybook/addon-docs/angular`**, and Compodoc integration:

---

## 📚 Storybook + Angular + Compodoc: `setCompodocJson` Setup

### 🔧 Standard Configuration (Official Docs)

Storybook for Angular is a framework that makes it easy to develop and test UI components in isolation. It uses Angular builders and integrates with Compodoc to provide automatic documentation generation.

To set up Compodoc, in your `.storybook/preview.ts`, add:


```ts
import type { Preview } from '@storybook/angular';
// 👇 Add these
import { setCompodocJson } from '@storybook/addon-docs/angular';
import docJson from '../documentation.json';

setCompodocJson(docJson);

const preview: Preview = {
  // ...
};
export default preview;
```


And in your `angular.json`, enable compodoc for both storybook and build-storybook targets:


```json
"build-storybook": {
  "builder": "@storybook/angular:build-storybook",
  "options": {
    "compodoc": true,
    "compodocArgs": ["-e", "json", "-d", "."]
  }
}
```


---

### ✅ Compodoc is Now Built-In

Note that Compodoc is now built into `@storybook/angular`; you don't have to call it explicitly. If you were running Compodoc in your `package.json` scripts, you can remove the related script.

The old scripts approach (before it was built-in):

```json
{ "scripts": {
  "docs:json": "compodoc -p tsconfig.json -e json -d ./documentation",
  "storybook": "npm run docs:json && start-storybook -p 6006"
}}
```
Should now be replaced with:
```json
{ "scripts": {
  "storybook": "ng run <project-name>:storybook",
  "build-storybook": "ng run <project-name>:build-storybook"
}}
```


---

### 🐛 Known Issue in Storybook 10 (Angular 20): Module Not Found

A bug has been reported where, after initializing Storybook (v10), TypeScript throws: `error TS2307: Cannot find module '@storybook/addon-docs/angular' or its corresponding type declarations`, triggered specifically by the line `import { setCompodocJson } from "@storybook/addon-docs/angular"`.

The bug was reported by a user trying to set up Storybook for a project using Angular 20 + Ionic 8. Running `npm create storybook@latest` fails at the end with `Error: Unknown argument: silent`.

The installed package versions in this case were: `storybook@^10.2.16`, `@storybook/angular@^10.2.16`, `@storybook/addon-docs@^10.2.16`, and `@compodoc/compodoc@^1.2.1`.

---

### 🏗️ Nx Workspace Setup

For Nx monorepos, in your project's `.storybook/preview.ts`, the import looks the same — `import { setCompodocJson } from '@storybook/addon-docs/angular'` — and you also need to add `"resolveJsonModule": true` in your `.storybook/tsconfig.json` to be able to import the `documentation.json` file.

When you run Compodoc, it generates a `documentation.json` file. Storybook then uses that file to render the documentation in the Docs tab.

---

### 🔁 Alternative: Using `globalThis` / parameters instead of `setCompodocJson`

An older GitHub issue suggested that rather than using `setCompodocJson` as a public API, a cleaner alternative might be:


```ts
// preview.ts
import compodocJson from 'path/to/compodoc/documentation.json';
export const parameters = {
  docs: { documentation: compodocJson }
}
```


---

### Summary

| Topic | Detail |
|---|---|
| Import path | `@storybook/addon-docs/angular` |
| Function | `setCompodocJson(docJson)` |
| Config file | `.storybook/preview.ts` |
| Built-in support | ✅ Yes, since recent `@storybook/angular` versions |
| Storybook 10 bug | ⚠️ Module not found error reported with Angular 20 |
| Nx support | ✅ Yes, with `resolveJsonModule: true` |

If you're hitting the **module not found** error in Storybook 10, it is a [known open issue on GitHub](https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/issues/34070) and may require a patch or workaround until it's resolved officially.


